The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | 11 killed in flurry of road mishaps
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      11 killed in flurry of road mishaps
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Eleven persons, including a traffic cop, died in half a dozen road mishaps in the city on Sunday and Monday.        
	Monirul Islam, a 45-year-old constable of the Calcutta police East Traffic Guard, was hit by a car at the Queens Park and Asutosh Chowdhury Avenue crossing around 8.30pm on Sunday.        
	He was standing beside the road and manning traffic. The driver lost control and hit him in the legs. Islam was admitted to Calcutta National Medical College and later to CMRI, where he died on Monday morning, said an officer. The driver of the car, Amrito Mukherjee, was arrested.        
	In another accident, five men on board a Tata mini-truck were killed when it collided with a truck on Southern Avenue around 1.15am on Sunday. The mini-truck was moving down the wrong lane.        
	Sintu Mal, 18, Ananda Panja, 25, Tubai, 20 and Gora, 25, died on the spot. The driver, 29-year-old Bijoy Barui, succumbed to his injuries at SSKM Hospital.        
	The men in the mini-truck were residents of Roy Bahadur Road in Behala. The lorry driver is absconding. His help has been admitted to SSKM Hospital, said an officer of Lake police station.        
	Another Tata mini-truck that was moving down the wrong side of the road mowed down a 38-year-old motorcyclist, Sunil Shaw, on Lockgate flyover on Sunday morning. Shaw was pronounced dead at RG Kar hospital. The driver was arrested.        
	On Sunday evening, 66-year-old Nirmala Das was mowed down by a truck on Diamond Harbour Road near her home in Manton. Witnesses alleged the driver was dozing in the cabin while his drunk help was at the wheel. The help was admitted to Vidyasagar State General Hospital after being beaten up by a mob.         
	A few hours later, seven persons sleeping on an SN Banerjee Road footpath were run over by a minibus. The seven were taken to Calcutta Medical College and Hospital where Ram Chandra Mahato, 60, was declared dead. Ram Subhrat Sahani, 55, died later. The other five are under treatment at the hospital. The minibus driver fled.        
	On Monday evening, Ameen Yadav, 68, died after a taxi hit him at Government Place West, near Town Hall. The driver fled.                                                                                                                                                          
